520etc%2520File%252088&amp;w=128&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FGeneral%2520Material%2520Birds%2520etc%2520File%252088&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FGeneral%2520Material%2520Birds%2520etc%2520File%252088&amp;w=256&amp;q=75\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">GENERAL MATERIAL BIRDS</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->Field reports complied in the Supplementary Nigerian Gazette 1937 and the Nigerian Field Journal 1939.</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p>1939</p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 -960 960 960\" width=\"24px\" fill=\"#1D1911\"><path d=\"M480-80 240-320l57-57 183 183 183-183 57 57L480-80ZM298-584l-58-56 240-240 240 240-58 56-182-182-182 182Z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class=\"my-16\"><div id=\"672b60cba0951c001ba0f703\" class=\"flex sm:flex-row flex-col justify-between border-black border-[1px]  font-montserrat transition-all font-light  p-2 gap-4 cursor-pointer bg-background\" style=\"width:180px;height:fit-content;position:relative;z-index:0;left:0;top:0;cursor:pointer\"><div style=\"width:100%\" class=\"flex flex-col gap-8 w-[100%] min-w-0 h-[100%] justify-between relative \"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;max-width:100%\"><img style=\"display:block;max-width:100%;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20version=%271.1%27%20width=%27100%27%20height=%27100%27/%3e\"/></span><img alt=\"cover page\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" class=\"object-contain\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\"/><noscript><img alt=\"cover page\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\" class=\"object-contain\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FIbo%2520Body%2520Painting%2520File%252014&amp;w=128&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FIbo%2520Body%2520Painting%2520File%252014&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FIbo%2520Body%2520Painting%2520File%252014&amp;w=256&amp;q=75\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">IBO BODY PAINTING FILE 14</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->A research carried out on body painting among the Ibo people. The different ways the girls and women decorated their bodies with paintings for festivals and dances. The boys during adolescence and up to the time of joining adult society used body painting as well. The different designs include patterns that consists of a few basic shapes such as a hook, a crescent, a triangle with concave sides, a rosette, a circle or dot, a right angle and straight and curved parallel lines and crossed radiating lines.</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p>1971</p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.or