ss=\"object-contain\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FIbo%2520Fishing%2520File%252018&amp;w=128&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FIbo%2520Fishing%2520File%252018&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FIbo%2520Fishing%2520File%252018&amp;w=256&amp;q=75\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">IBO FISHING FILE</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->Notes on various Fish traps made in Abriba, Ogba Clan, Ekpeye Clan, Ekpeya Clan, Ukpo etc.</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p>1939</p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 -960 960 960\" width=\"24px\" fill=\"#1D1911\"><path d=\"M480-80 240-320l57-57 183 183 183-183 57 57L480-80ZM298-584l-58-56 240-240 240 240-58 56-182-182-182 182Z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class=\"my-16\"><div id=\"672b61aba0951c001ba0f707\" class=\"flex sm:flex-row flex-col justify-between border-black border-[1px]  font-montserrat transition-all font-light  p-2 gap-4 cursor-pointer bg-background\" style=\"width:180px;height:fit-content;position:relative;z-index:0;left:0;top:0;cursor:pointer\"><div style=\"width:100%\" class=\"flex flex-col gap-8 w-[100%] min-w-0 h-[100%] justify-between relative \"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;max-width:100%\"><img style=\"display:block;max-width:100%;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20version=%271.1%27%20width=%27100%27%20height=%27100%27/%3e\"/></span><img alt=\"cover page\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" class=\"object-contain\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\"/><noscript><img alt=\"cover page\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\" class=\"object-contain\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FIbo%2520woodcarving%2520File%252022&amp;w=128&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FIbo%2520woodcarving%2520File%252022&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FIbo%2520woodcarving%2520File%252022&amp;w=256&amp;q=75\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">IBO WOOD CARVING</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->The file entails information on the Ekwerazu clan, their work on figure carvings, some of which are very good. Others include; painting, modelling, calabash making, fishing, baskets, etc. Agbaja clan are seen to be timid in the Division which is shown in their markets by pricing and selling articles to a European far below the real price. There are fair amount of very good religious figure carving, but its not easy to see.</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p>1937</p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 -960 960 960\" width=\"24px\" fill=\"#1D1911\"><path d=\"M480-80 240-320l57-57 183 183 183-183 57 57L480-80ZM298-584l-58-56 240-240 240 240-58 56-182-182-182 182Z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class=\"my-16\"><div id=\"672b61cca0951c001ba0f708\" class=\"flex sm:flex-row flex-col justify-between border-black border-[1px]  font-montserrat transition-all font-light  p-2 gap-4 cursor-pointer bg-background\" style=\"width:180px;height:fit-content;position:relative;z-index:0;left:0;top:0;cursor:pointer\"><div style=\"width:100%\" class=\"flex flex-col gap-8 w-[100%] min-w-0 h-[100%] justify-between relative \"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;max-width:100%\"><img style=\"display:block;max-width:100%;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20version=%271.1%27%20width=%27100%27%20height=%27100%27/%3e\"/></span><img alt=\"cover page\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" class=\"object-contain\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\"/><noscript><img alt=\"cover page\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\" class=\"object-contain\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A