mage?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FMetalwork%2520file%2520106&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FMetalwork%2520file%2520106&amp;w=256&amp;q=75\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">METAL WORK FILE 106</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->Instruments made of Metal in ibo Culture, such as Hoes, Staff, Knives and Musical instrument, Gong</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p></p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 -960 960 960\" width=\"24px\" fill=\"#1D1911\"><path d=\"M480-80 240-320l57-57 183 183 183-183 57 57L480-80ZM298-584l-58-56 240-240 240 240-58 56-182-182-182 182Z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class=\"my-16\"><div id=\"672b6249a0951c001ba0f70b\" class=\"flex sm:flex-row flex-col justify-between border-black border-[1px]  font-montserrat transition-all font-light  p-2 gap-4 cursor-pointer bg-background\" style=\"width:180px;height:fit-content;position:relative;z-index:0;left:0;top:0;cursor:pointer\"><div style=\"width:100%\" class=\"flex flex-col gap-8 w-[100%] min-w-0 h-[100%] justify-between relative \"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;max-width:100%\"><img style=\"display:block;max-width:100%;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20version=%271.1%27%20width=%27100%27%20height=%27100%27/%3e\"/></span><img alt=\"cover page\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" class=\"object-contain\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\"/><noscript><img alt=\"cover page\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\" class=\"object-contain\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FNorthern%2520Pottery%2520File%252092&amp;w=128&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FNorthern%2520Pottery%2520File%252092&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FNorthern%2520Pottery%2520File%252092&amp;w=256&amp;q=75\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">NORTHERN POTTERY FILE</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->The file entails processes of making pots in Okene, Kaura, Namoda amongst others and the type of pots seen were spherical jars for water. Pottery at Daura is done at Kando, Yerdoji, Gwado and Sara, in Katagun Division, a few women make pots, in Sokoto and Bauchi, men and women make pots, in Kastina, pots are made at Kashi, Kaltungo. At Jaba, pottery is done by women and the tools used include: Touror, Kwon, Soso among others.</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p>1945</p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 -960 960 960\" width=\"24px\" fill=\"#1D1911\"><path d=\"M480-80 240-320l57-57 183 183 183-183 57 57L480-80ZM298-584l-58-56 240-240 240 240-58 56-182-182-182 182Z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class=\"my-16\"><div id=\"672b625fa0951c001ba0f70d\" class=\"flex sm:flex-row flex-col justify-between border-black border-[1px]  font-montserrat transition-all font-light  p-2 gap-4 cursor-pointer bg-background\" style=\"width:180px;height:fit-content;position:relative;z-index:0;left:0;top:0;cursor:pointer\"><div style=\"width:100%\" class=\"flex flex-col gap-8 w-[100%] min-w-0 h-[100%] justify-between relative \"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;max-width:100%\"><img style=\"display:block;max-width:100%;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20version=%271.1%27%20width=%27100%27%20height=%27100%27/%3e\"/></span><img alt=\"cover page\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" class=\"object-contain\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\"/><noscript><img alt=\"cover page\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\" class=\"object-contain\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FOboro%2520etc_3&amp;w=128&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FOboro%2520etc_3&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FOboro%2520etc_3&amp;w=256&amp;q=75\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">OBORO</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->A written report on the petitions on the Apese Village and a field report on some cultural and traditional practices in the Oboro clan such as, rejoicing at birth, sickness in the clan, etc..</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p>1931</p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 -960 960 960\" width=\"24px\" fill=\"#1D1911\"><path d=\"M480-80 240-320l57-57 183 183 183-183 57 57L480-80ZM298-584l-58-56 240-240 240 240-58 56-182-182-182 182Z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class=\"my-16\"><div id=\"672b6297a0951c001ba0f70e\" class=\"flex sm:flex-row flex-col justify-between border-black border-[1px]  font-montserrat transition-all font-light  p-2 gap-4 cursor-pointer bg-background\" style=\"width:180px;height:fit-content;position:relative;z-index:0;left:0;top:0;cursor:pointer\"><div style=\"width:100%\" class=\"flex flex-col gap-8 w-[100%] min-w-0 h-[100%] justify-between relative \"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;max-width:100%\"><img style=\"display:block;max-width:100%;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20version=%271.1%27%20width=%27100%27%20height=%27100%27/%3e\"/></span><img alt=\"cover page\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" class=\"object-contain\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\"/><noscript><img alt=\"cover page\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\" class=\"object-contain\" srcSet=\"/assets/imageSkel.svg 1x, /assets/imageSkel.svg 2x\" src=\"/assets/imageSkel.svg\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">P.A ALLISON</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->The file has correspondence from Benard Fagg on behalf og P.A Allison asking for a post in the Department of Antiquity, also letters from B.D Dixey giving recommendation about P.A Allision</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p>1961</p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 -960 960 960\" width=\"24px\" fill=\"#1D1911\"><path d=\"M480-80 240-320l57-57 183 183 183-183 57 57L480-80ZM298-584l-58-56 240-240 240 240-58 56-182-182-182 182Z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class=\"my-16\"><div id=\"672b62aba0951c001ba0f70f\" class=\"flex sm:flex-row flex-col justify-between border-black border-[1px]  font-montserrat transition-all font-light  p-2 gap-4 cursor-pointer bg-background\" style=\"width:180px;height:fit-content;position:relative;z-index:0;left:0;top:0;cursor:pointer\"><div style=\"width:100%\" class=\"flex flex-col gap-8 w-[100%] min-w-0 h-[100%] justify-between relative \"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;max-width:100%\"><img style=\"display:block;max-width:100%;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20version=%271.1%27%20width=%27100%27%20height=%27100%27/%3e\"/></span><img alt=\"cover page\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" class=\"object-contain\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\"/><noscript><img alt=\"cover page\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\" class=\"object-contain\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FPottery%2520Omu%2520notes%2520Files%252068&amp;w=128&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FPottery%2520Omu%2520notes%2520Files%252068&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FPottery%2520Omu%2520notes%2520Files%252068&amp;w=256&amp;q=75\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">POTTERY OMU</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->The field work was carried out to study methods of making pots in different stages, such as Ikoko Orisha Apa, Odu, they are large pots used for cooking yam flour (Elubo), Enigun are small pots. This information are backed up with pictures.</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p></p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 -960 960 960\" width=\"24px\" fill=\"#1D1911\"><path d=\"M480-80 240-320l57-57 183 183 183-183 57 57L480-80ZM298-584l-58-56 240-240 240 240-58 56-182-182-182 182Z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class=\"my-16\"><div id=\"672b6317a0951c001ba0f710\" class=\"flex sm:flex-row flex-col justify-between border-black border-[1px]  font-montserrat transition-all font-light  p-2 gap-4 cursor-pointer bg-background\" style=\"width:180px;height:fit-content;position:relative;z-index:0;left:0;top:0;cursor:pointer\"><div style=\"width:100%\" class=\"flex flex-col gap-8 w-[100%] min-w-0 h-[100%] justify-between relative \"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;max-width:100%\"><img style=\"display:block;max-width:100%;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20version=%271.1%27%20width=%27100%27%20height=%27100%27/%3e\"/></span><img alt=\"cover page\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" class=\"object-contain\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\"/><noscript><img alt=\"cover page\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\" class=\"object-contain\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FSokoto%2520File%252044_&amp;w=128&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FSokoto%2520File%252044_&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FSokoto%2520File%252044_&amp;w=256&amp;q=75\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">SOKOTO FILE</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->Notes complied by C.K. Meek of field reports by C. Hercules Read, G.W. Webster on Sokoto Provincial Gazettes, Arugungun among others.</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p>1925</p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 -960 960 960\" width=\"24px\" fill=\"#1D1911\"><path d=\"M480-80 240-320l57-57 183 183 183-183 57 57L480-80ZM298-584l-58-56 240-240 240 240-58 56-182-182-182 182Z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class=\"my-16\"><div id=\"672b632ca0951c001ba0f711\" class=\"flex sm:flex-row flex-col justify-between border-black border-[1px]  font-montserrat transition-all font-light  p-2 gap-4 cursor-pointer bg-background\" style=\"width:180px;height:fit-content;position:relative;z-index:0;left:0;top:0;cursor:pointer\"><div style=\"width:100%\" class=\"flex flex-col gap-8 w-[100%] min-w-0 h-[100%] justify-between relative \"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;max-width:100%\"><img style=\"display:block;max-width:100%;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20version=%271.1%27%20width=%27100%27%20height=%27100%27/%3e\"/></span><img alt=\"cover page\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" class=\"object-contain\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\"/><noscript><img alt=\"cover page\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\" class=\"object-contain\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FW.B%2520Fagg_2&amp;w=128&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FW.B%2520Fagg_2&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FW.B%2520Fagg_2&amp;w=256&amp;q=75\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">W.B FAGG</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->Letters written between W.B. Fagg and K.C. Murray about their experiences on the field.</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p>1945</p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 -960 960 960\" width=\"24px\" fill=\"#1D1911\"><path d=\"M480-80 240-320l57-57 183 183 183-183 57 57L480-80ZM298-584l-58-56 240-240 240 240-58 56-182-182-182 182Z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class=\"my-16\"><div id=\"672b6343a0951c001ba0f712\" class=\"flex sm:flex-row flex-col justify-between border-black border-[1px]  font-montserrat transition-all font-light  p-2 gap-4 cursor-pointer bg-background\" style=\"width:180px;height:fit-content;position:relative;z-index:0;left:0;top:0;cursor:pointer\"><div style=\"width:100%\" class=\"flex flex-col gap-8 w-[100%] min-w-0 h-[100%] justify-between relative \"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;max-width:100%\"><img style=\"display:block;max-width:100%;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20version=%271.1%27%20width=%27100%27%20height=%27100%27/%3e\"/></span><img alt=\"cover page\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" class=\"object-contain\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\"/><noscript><img alt=\"cover page\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"intrinsic\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%\" class=\"object-contain\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FYoruba%2520calabash%2520carving%2520File%252073&amp;w=128&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FYoruba%2520calabash%2520carving%2520File%252073&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Flagosmuseumarchives.ng%2Fapi%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2FYoruba%2520calabash%2520carving%2520File%252073&amp;w=256&amp;q=75\"/></noscript></span><div class=\"\"><h3 class=\"font-semibold uppercase break-words text-[0.8rem] pb-4\">YORUBA CALABASH FILE 73</h3><p class=\" font-light text-[0.75rem] \"> <!-- -->The document consists of information on Calabash carving, Instrum,ents used for carving Calabash include: Oloko, Gangan, Aregba, Pala, Ifingba. Designs are made on the calabash, such as Incised design and raised design\nthe Calabash in Yoruba land, particularly in Abeokuta area include, Koto, Igba Ademu, Ato, Age, Keregbe, Pakata, igba, igbaje, Igbako, Alta</p></div><div class=\"flex justify-between p-4  bottom-2 \"><p>1949</p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 -960 960 960\" width=\"24px\" fill=\"#1D1911\"><path d=\"M480-80 240-320l57-57 183 183 183-183 57 57L480-80ZM298-584l-58-56 240-240 240 240-58 56-182-182-182 182Z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"flex gap-4 items-center justify-center text-sm py-6 border-t border-primary\"><button disabled=\"\" class=\"px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-background disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed hover:opacity-80\">First</button><button disabled=\"\" class=\"px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-background disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed hover:opacity-80\">Previous</button><span class=\"text-primary font-semibold\">Page <!-- -->1<!-- --> of <!-- -->3</span><button class=\"px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-background disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed hover:opacity-80\">Next</button><button class=\"px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-background disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed hover:opacity-80\">Last</button></div></div></div></div><div class=\"w-[100vw] bg-black h-[100vh] top-0 absolute\" style=\"width:100vw\"></div></article><!--$--><!--/$--></div><script>$RC(\"B:1\",\"S:1\")</s