holtz on field work on stone implements by Dr. A.D.N. Bain with S.W. Walker on their visit to Dobeli. It also entails the discovery of Iron remains in Muri Division in 1832 and the field report from Yola Adamawa Province on festivals, Mumuye Tribe, Bachama Tribe, Kilba and Margi Tribes, among others.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1931\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":220,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"ADAMAWA STONE IMPLEMENT\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:18:17.283Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:18:17.283Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/ADAMAWA%20STONE%20IMPLEMENT-2.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"ADAMAWA STONE IMPLEMENT-2.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":2699037,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"H.J. Braunholtz, S.W. Walker, A.D.N. Bain\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Stone, Implement, Discovery, Iron, Yola, Adamawa Province, Cult Objects, Calabash, Canoes, Pottery\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"ADAMAWA STONE IMPLEMENT\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Adamawa Province\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"ADAMAWA STONE IMPLEMENT\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b5e90a0951c001ba0f6fc\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"BAMBOO AND SLATED WORK\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":346,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Bamboo and slated work file\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T09:53:53.151Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T09:53:53.151Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Bamboo%20and%20slated%20work%20file\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Bamboo and slated work file\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":249336,\\\"width\\\":2176,\\\"height\\\":2824,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"A report which entails information with drawings of a tray for hanging in the roof of a house, made at Okpur Ahaba in Ngwa clan. Okeri Azu seen at Inyeogugu used for storing fish, the base is made of palm ribs details of Abo Ogugu, made at Asaga, Ohaifa. Mpokoro seen at Ihite, Ezenhitte clan, used for storing yam under the roof of a house. Alto Oko seen at Abriba, a box used for storing meat, made at Owutu Edda, Afikpo, Obeda, a tray about eighteen inches in diameter used for hanging above a fire for drying fish among others.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":null,\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":221,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"BAMBOO AND SLATED WORK\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:18:42.649Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:18:42.649Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/BAMBOO%20AND%20SLATED%20WORK.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"BAMBOO AND SLATED WORK.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":1385987,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"National Commission For Museums and Monuments.\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Bamboo, Roof, Abiriba, Afikpo, Ibo\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"BAMBOO AND SLATED WORK\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Eastern Province\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"BAMBOO AND SLATED WORK\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b5ea7a0951c001ba0f6fd\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"DRAWING AND BASKETRY\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":363,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Drawings of basketry file 111\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T08:57:17.728Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T08:57:17.728Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Drawings%20of%20basketry%20file%20111\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Drawings of basketry file 111\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":53502,\\\"width\\\":1720,\\\"height\\\":2528,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"The report contains a short note on the basket seen at Amokwe, Item (Bende Division) which is from Ogoja Division, it is said that people are trying to make it locally. It is used as a box and made of bunches of grass. The coiled baskets at Ekwerazu are called Egede Achara.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":null,\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":222,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"DRAWING AND BASKETRY\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:19:11.046Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:19:11.046Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/DRAWING%20AND%20BASKETRY.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"DRAWING AND BASKETRY.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":348982,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K.C. Murray\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Drawing, Basketry, Ogoja Division, Bende, Coiled Basket\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"DRAWING AND BASKETRY\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Ogoja Division, Bende Division, Eastern Province\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"DRAWING AND BASKETRY\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b5ecaa0951c001ba0f6fe\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"EKITI FILE 60\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":361,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Ekiti etc File 60\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T08:35:06.726Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T08:35:06.726Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Ekiti%20etc%20File%2060\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Ekiti etc File 60\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":242562,\\\"width\\\":1876,\\\"height\\\":2672,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"Ekiti File entails lists and notes on Yoruba customs in Ilaje, Arogbo villages with description of face masks and headdresses, bronze Bell, etc. Also there are notes on plays and festivals in Ilaje Community, fishing and mat making in places like Ugbo and Mahin. The document also entails extracts from intelligence report by R.J.M. Curwen, R.A. Vosper, T.B. Bovell-Jones, J.H. Beeley and N.A.C. Weir . There is a report on Antiquities at Owo ,appointment of native authorities and notes on Ekiti Division customs and traditions.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1943\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":223,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"EKITI FILE 60\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:20:36.487Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:20:36.487Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/EKITI%20FILE%2060.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"EKITI FILE 60.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":35249148,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K.C. Murray, R.J.M. Curwen, J.H. Beeley, T.B. Bovell-Jones, R.A. Vosper\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Face masks, Headdress, Bronze Bell, Festivals, Ilaje, Ekiti Division, Ondo Division, Trade Guild, Ivories, Native Authories, Ceremonial Sword, Iron, Brass, Beadwork, Pottery, Carved Post, Egungun Masks, Idanre, Weaving\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"EKITI FILE 60\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Ekiti Division, Ondo Division, Western Province\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"EKITI FILE 60\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b5fb9a0951c001ba0f700\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"EKITI\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":364,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Ekiti\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T09:00:20.223Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T09:00:20.223Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Ekiti\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Ekiti\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":16734,\\\"width\\\":892,\\\"height\\\":1376,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"A short description on objects such as, masks, iron staff and wood carving in different parts of Ekiti.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":null,\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":224,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"EKITI\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:23:37.025Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:23:37.025Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/EKITI.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"EKITI.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":336359,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K.C Murray\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Schedules, Ekiti, Masks, Wood Carving, Iron Staff\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"EKITI\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Ekiti District, Western Province.\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"EKITI\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b5fcfa0951c001ba0f701\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"GENERAL KILN FILE 90\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":366,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"General Kiln File 90\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T09:04:25.043Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T09:04:25.043Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/General%20Kiln%20File%2090\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"General Kiln File 90\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":166133,\\\"width\\\":1504,\\\"height\\\":2864,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"A report on pottery drawings, drawing of a small gas kiln, planning processes of pottery, materials required, and list of labor needed. Also there are Newspaper cuttings of pottery work in this manuscript.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1931\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":226,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"GENERAL KILN FILE\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:25:47.893Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:25:47.893Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/GENERAL%20KILN%20FILE-1.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"GENERAL KILN FILE-1.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":20000388,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K. C. Murray, Newsapers\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Umuhunta, Pottery, Drawings, Newspaper, Gas Kiln\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"GENERAL KILN FILE 90\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Umuhunta, Eastern Province, Nigeria.\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"GENERAL KILN FILE\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b6092a0951c001ba0f702\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"GENERAL MATERIAL BIRDS\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":348,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"General Material Birds etc File 88\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T10:08:24.977Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T10:08:24.977Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/General%20Material%20Birds%20etc%20File%2088\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"General Material Birds etc File 88\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":25097,\\\"width\\\":956,\\\"height\\\":1444,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"Field reports complied in the Supplementary Nigerian Gazette 1937 and the Nigerian Field Journal 1939.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1939\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":227,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"GENERAL MATERIAL BIRDS\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:27:39.665Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:27:39.665Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/GENERAL%20MATERIAL%20BIRDS.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"GENERAL MATERIAL BIRDS.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":10230705,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"Supplement to the Nigeria Gazette The Journal of the Nigerian Field Society, K.C. Murray\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Field Journal, Nigerian Gazette, Field work, K.C. Murray\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"GENERAL MATERIAL BIRDS\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Nigeria\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"GENERAL MATERIAL BIRDS\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b60cba0951c001ba0f703\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"IBO BODY PAINTING FILE 14\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":356,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Ibo Body Painting File 14\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T13:00:56.379Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T13:00:56.379Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Ibo%20Body%20Painting%20File%2014\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Ibo Body Painting File 14\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":28210,\\\"width\\\":960,\\\"height\\\":1472,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"A research carried out on body painting among the Ibo people. The different ways the girls and women decorated their bodies with paintings for festivals and dances. The boys during adolescence and up to the time of joining adult society used body painting as well. The different designs include patterns that consists of a few basic shapes such as a hook, a crescent, a triangle with concave sides, a rosette, a circle or dot, a right angle and straight and curved parallel lines and crossed radiating lines.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1971\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":228,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"IBO BODY PAINTING\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:28:36.100Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:28:36.100Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/IBO%20BODY%20PAINTING.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"IBO BODY PAINTING.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":10636701,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K.C Murray\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Ibo, Body Painting, Decoration, Umuahia, Ogoja Province\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"IBO BODY PAINTING FILE 14\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Umuahia, Ogoja Division, Eastern Province\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"IBO BODY PAINTING\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b6134a0951c001ba0f704\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"IBO FISHING FILE\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":355,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Ibo Fishing File 18\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T12:56:41.196Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T12:56:41.196Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Ibo%20Fishing%20File%2018\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Ibo Fishing File 18\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":34897,\\\"width\\\":944,\\\"height\\\":1176,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"Notes on various Fish traps made in Abriba, Ogba Clan, Ekpeye Clan, Ekpeya Clan, Ukpo etc.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1939\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":231,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"IBO FISHING FILE\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:31:12.341Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:31:12.341Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/IBO%20FISHING%20FILE.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"IBO FISHING FILE.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":2320603,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K.C Murray\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Ibo, Canoe, Fish Trap, Clan\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"IBO FISHING FILE\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Eastern Province\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"IBO FISHING FILE\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b61aba0951c001ba0f707\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"IBO WOOD CARVING\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":354,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Ibo woodcarving File 22\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T11:30:19.515Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T11:30:19.515Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Ibo%20woodcarving%20File%2022\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Ibo woodcarving File 22\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":29356,\\\"width\\\":972,\\\"height\\\":1468,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"The file entails information on the Ekwerazu clan, their work on figure carvings, some of which are very good. Others include; painting, modelling, calabash making, fishing, baskets, etc. Agbaja clan are seen to be timid in the Division which is shown in their markets by pricing and selling articles to a European far below the real price. There are fair amount of very good religious figure carving, but its not easy to see.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1937\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":232,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"IBO WOOD CARVING\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:32:04.681Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:32:04.681Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/IBO%20WOOD%20CARVING-1.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"IBO WOOD CARVING-1.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":6320728,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K.C. Murray\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Ibo, Wood Carving, Figures, Ekwerazu, Agbaja\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"IBO WOOD CARVING\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Owerri Division, Onitsha Division, Eastern Provinces\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"IBO WOOD CARVING\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b61cca0951c001ba0f708\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"IDOMA MOULDING\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":439,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Idoma moulding and figures\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-25T11:27:06.127Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-25T11:27:06.127Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Idoma%20moulding%20and%20figures-3.Idoma%20moulding%20and%20figures\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Idoma moulding and figures-3.Idoma moulding and figures\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":490900,\\\"width\\\":3740,\\\"height\\\":2080,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"Incidence that took place during K.C Murray's visit to some Yoruba villages, including interviews with a Yoruba elders (Adu Adamson of Inupa). Apese village about canoe making in Lagos and notes of Apese village and fishing and fishermen on Victoria Beach.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1929\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":233,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"IDOMA MOULDING\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:33:04.270Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:33:04.270Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/IDOMA%20MOULDING.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"IDOMA MOULDING.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":25335946,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K.C Murray\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Fishing, Canoe, Apese, Yoruba\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"IDOMA MOULDING\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Apese, Lagos, Nigeria\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"IDOMA MOULDING\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b6218a0951c001ba0f709\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"ILOJO BAR\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":352,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Ilojo Bar_2\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T10:43:40.927Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T10:43:40.927Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Ilojo%20Bar_2\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Ilojo Bar_2\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":44477,\\\"width\\\":888,\\\"height\\\":1408,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"Antiquities ordinances and evaluation of Ilojo Bar, as well as statement of Policy of the establishment of Museums in Nigeria.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1958\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":234,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"ILOJO BAR\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:33:46.872Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:33:46.872Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/ILOJO%20BAR.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"ILOJO BAR.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":1849086,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"Benard Fagg\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Ilojo Bar, Bernard Fagg, Letters\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"ILOJO BAR\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Lagos\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"ILOJO BAR\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b6231a0951c001ba0f70a\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"METAL WORK FILE 106\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":440,\