:{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K.C. Murray, A.C. Callaway\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Letters, Annual Report, K.C. Murray, A.C. Callaway\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"YORUBA MINCE INDUSTRIES\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Nigeria and London\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"YORUBA MINCE INDUSTRIES\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b63d1a0951c001ba0f717\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"YORUBA OMU 67\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":373,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Yoruba Omu File 67\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T10:10:20.175Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T10:10:20.175Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Yoruba%20Omu%20File%2067\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Yoruba Omu File 67\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":27832,\\\"width\\\":1064,\\\"height\\\":1632,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"The report entails notes on Yoruba potters such as Bandele, Adebola, Iyola and the process of pottery making. The potters generally go in groups in the early morning to get clay and help each other with the digging. Firing of pots is done at Omu Aran, pots are to be finished as black ware, notably Isasun and Awo pots are given a thorough polishing with a pebble before firing. It also includes notes on the process of firing, drying and repairs.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":null,\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":247,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"YORUBA OMU\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:41:09.841Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:41:09.841Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/YORUBA%20OMU.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"YORUBA OMU.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":7290215,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K.C. Murray\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Pottery, Omu-Aran, Ekiti\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"YORUBA OMU 67\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Omu-Aran, Ekiti Province, Nigeria.\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"YORUBA OMU\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b6418a0951c001ba0f719\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"YORUBA WEAVING\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":353,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Yoruba Weaving File 74\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T11:06:55.652Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-15T11:06:55.652Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Yoruba%20Weaving%20File%2074\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Yoruba Weaving File 74\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":305756,\\\"width\\\":2020,\\\"height\\\":2556,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"A field work carried out on cloth weaving in different parts of Ondo and Ilorin Province, for example: Aso Ofi.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1933\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":248,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"YORUBA WEAVING\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:42:46.035Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:42:46.035Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/YORUBA%20WEAVING.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"YORUBA WEAVING.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":13283411,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K.C. Murray\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Yoruba, Weaving, Technology, Field work\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"YORUBA WEAVING\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Ondo and Ilorin Province\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"YORUBA WEAVING\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"672b649fa0951c001ba0f71a\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"YORUBA, IFE, ILLA\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":359,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Yoruba ife and iila\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T08:27:47.765Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-19T08:27:47.765Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Yoruba%20ife%20and%20iila\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Yoruba ife and iila\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":239380,\\\"width\\\":2212,\\\"height\\\":2800,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"Yoruba, Ife, Illa file entails notes on; festivals, history, crafts, sites, list of mythical, historical and religious personages. The notes on bead making at Ife and Kaura Mamoda. Beads were being made at Ife thirty years ago by two women in Ilode and men of the Ajilesoro family who lived on the Ibadan side of Ife. It also consists of the Yoruba calendar , festivals like; Ifa festival, Olojo festival, as well as notes on the origin of Egungun and Oro cult.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1944\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":249,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"YORUBA, IFE, ILLA\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:45:02.552Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-06T12:45:02.552Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/YORUBA%2C%20IFE%2C%20ILLA.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"YORUBA, IFE, ILLA.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":18583036,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"K.C. Murray, W. R. Bascom\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Yoruba, Ife, Illa, Festival, Orisha, Egungun, Newspaper\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"YORUBA, IFE, ILLA\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"Western Provinces\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"YORUBA, IFE, ILLA\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"673df2a8a7f2f7001bd2eb39\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Dance and Plays file 80\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":421,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Dance and Plays file 80\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2025-02-05T11:17:13.097Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-21T10:57:31.002Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Danced%20and%20Plays%20file%2080\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Danced and Plays file 80\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":0,\\\"width\\\":2096,\\\"height\\\":2848,\\\"focalX\\\":50,\\\"focalY\\\":50,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"description\\\":\\\"The file entails definition of dance, ritual, drama, rhythmic movement, gestures, the description of dance for instance, Bolewa Dancing, Fulani perspective of dance, Hevehe festival and dramatic dance . Also a write up on World History of the Dance by Curt Sachs, and an article written by Fela Showande on Nigerian Review(No. 58) on Keeping West Africa Alive in West African Music.\\\",\\\"creation\\\":\\\"1938\\\",\\\"accession\\\":\\\"1959\\\",\\\"file\\\":{\\\"id\\\":416,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"DANCE AND PLAYS.pdf\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-20T14:33:01.359Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-20T14:33:01.359Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/DANCE%20AND%20PLAYS.pdf\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"DANCE AND PLAYS.pdf\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":6364248,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"focalX\\\":null,\\\"focalY\\\":null,\\\"sizes\\\":{\\\"thumb\\\":{\\\"url\\\":null,\\\"width\\\":null,\\\"height\\\":null,\\\"mimeType\\\":null,\\\"filesize\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":null}}},\\\"authors\\\":\\\"Curt Sachs Fela Showande\\\",\\\"keyword\\\":\\\"Dance, Plays, Festivals, Bolewa, Ritual, Drama, Hevehe Festival, Fulani Dance, Dance History\\\",\\\"condition\\\":\\\"fair\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"National Museum Lagos\\\",\\\"rights\\\":null,\\\"identifiers\\\":\\\"Dance and Plays file 80\\\",\\\"provenance\\\":\\\"West Africa\\\",\\\"slug\\\":null,\\\"blockName\\\":\\\"Dance and Plays File 80\\\",\\\"blockType\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"673f37d70d80f5001a616706\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Cameroon\\\",\\\"image\\\":{\\\"id\\\":422,\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Camerouns\\\",\\\"prefix\\\":\\\"media\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-21T13:39:19.609Z\\\",\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2024-11-21T13:39:19.609Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/Camerouns\\\",\\\"thumbnailURL\\\":null,\\\"filename\\\":\\\"Camerouns\\\",\\\"mimeType\\\":\\\"image/jpeg\\\",\\\"filesize\\\":132941,